isoforms from RBMYB and RBMY were combined and reanalyzed:

I saw that there was RBMY and RBMYB last time (YAGs_20251015), 
and this is the combined version of those two genes. I clustered them, 
and observed that all the entries in RBMYB fall into one pre-existing 
cluster in RBMY (PanPan__RBMY_isoform_35__CGCCCTGGG__15_reads), 
without any change in clusters of RBMY.